onsive.png\" id=\"47493\" width=\"600\" height=\"500\" class=\"leftAlone ss-htmleditorfield-file image\"]</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,0,3,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,'Anyone','LoggedInUsers',0,0,6678,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Inherit','Inherit',NULL,0,0,0,0,1),(49795,6674,40,1,1,1,'Page','2012-05-25 08:28:48','2025-06-25 05:19:19','responsive','Responsive',NULL,'<p class=\"intro\">The Startup theme has been built using responsive styling. This means when you reduce the width of your browser window, the site will adapt to the screen size.</p>\n<div class=\"captionImage leftAlone\" style=\"width: 600px;\">[image src=\"/assets/Uploads/responsive.png\" id=\"47482\" width=\"600\" height=\"326\" class=\"leftAlone ss-htmleditorfield-file image\"]\n<p class=\"caption leftAlone\">Ministry of Science Innovation working responsively on difference devices</p>\n</div>\n<p>Responsive web design is an approach aimed at crafting sites to provide an optimal viewing experience - easy reading and navigation with minimal resizing, panning, and scrolling - across a wide range of devices (from mobile phones to desktop computer monitors).</p>\n<p>This behaviour is provided by the default with the theme. Alternatively, you can also view this page on your favourite smartphone to see how the theme adjusts to a specific device. The menus and other elements of the page will change to be mobile or tablet friendly.</p>\n<p>[image src=\"/assets/Uploads/0f0943bb26/theme-responsive.png\" id=\"47493\" width=\"600\" height=\"500\" class=\"leftAlone ss-htmleditorfield-file image\"]</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,0,3,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,'Anyone','LoggedInUsers',0,0,6678,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Inherit','Inherit',NULL,0,0,0,0,1),(49796,7197,18,0,1,0,'Page','2013-10-04 13:37:19','2025-06-25 05:20:27','silverstripe-cms','Silverstripe CMS',NULL,'<div class=\"captionImage leftAlone\" style=\"width: 600px;\">[image src=\"/assets/Uploads/cms-page-edit-small.png\" id=\"47483\" width=\"600\" height=\"468\" class=\"leftAlone ss-htmleditorfield-file image\"]\n<p class=\"caption leftAlone\">Silverstripe CMS interface</p>\n</div>\n<h3>Friendly and flexible open source CMS</h3>\n<p>The Silverstripe CMS is designed to promote accessible site design and semantic markup. With its template flexibility, we\'re confident that it will be able to accommodate whatever is coming next. It has been downloaded well over 500,000 times and powers websites for government agencies, corporations, non-profits and a large number of much smaller websites.</p>\n<p>We believe the open source model simply produces better web software and in turn, better meets our own needs and those of other developers who use the software. As with all open source software, anyone has access to the source code, and a global community of developers can share best practices, code, documentation, roadmap ideas and so on.</p>\n<p>You never have to pay a licensing fee for Silverstripe CMS, and you never have to worry about vendor lock-in. Under the BSD license, which is one of the most flexible open source licenses and Open Source Initiative approved, you benefit from the contributions of others in the community, and the transparent way in which the software is developed in consultation with its users.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,0,1,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,'Anyone','LoggedInUsers',0,0,102,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Inherit','Inherit',NULL,0,0,0,0,1),(49797,7197,19,1,1,1,'Page','2013-10-04 13:37:19','2025-06-25 05:20:27','silverstripe-cms','Silverstripe CMS',NULL,'<div class=\"captionImage leftAlone\" style=\"width: 600px;\">[image src=\"/assets/Uploads/cms-page-edit-small.png\" id=\"47483\" width=\"600\" height=\"468\" class=\"leftAlone ss-htmleditorfield-file image\"]\n<p class=\"caption leftAlone\">Silverstripe CMS interface</p>\n</div>\n<h3>Friendly and flexible open source CMS</h3>\n<p>The Silverstripe CMS is designed to promote accessible site design and semantic markup. With its template flexibility, we\'re confident that it will be able to accommodate whatever is coming next. It has been downloaded well over 500,000 times and powers websites for government agencies, corporations, non-profits and a large number of much smaller websites.</p>\n<p>We believe the open source model simply produces better web software and in turn, better meets our own needs and those of other developers who use the software. As with all open source software, anyone has access to the source code, and a global community of developers can share best practices, code, documentation, roadmap ideas and so on.</p>\n<p>You never have to pay a licensing fee for Silverstripe CMS, and you never have to worry about vendor lock-in. Under the BSD license, which is one of the most flexible open source licenses and Open Source Initiative approved, you benefit from the contributions of others in the community, and the transparent way in which the software is developed in consultation with its users.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,0,1,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,'Anyone','LoggedInUsers',0,0,102,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Inherit','Inherit',NULL,0,0,0,0,1),(49798,7198,12,0,1,0,'Page','2013-10-04 13:59:38','2025-06-25 05:20:47','silverstripe-framework','Silverstripe Framework',NULL,'<p><span class=\"intro\">Besides a powerful and intuitive content authoring application, the Silverstripe CMS contains a powerful PHP based framework. The Silverstripe Framework brings immense flexibility and ease in customising your site and provides fundamentals such as security models, workflow, caching as well as multiple language and sub-site support.</span></p>\n<h3>Under the hood</h3>\n<p>Behind the clean CMS and website presentation sits <a href=\"https://www.silverstripe.org/framework-introduction/\">Silverstripe Framework</a>. Website developers use the framework to write code to create templates, logic and tailor how the CMS works. Developers get the power and flexibility of modern PHP code, while content authors get the simplicity of a tailored CMS.</p>\n<p>[image src=\"/assets/Uploads/code.pn